<org.eclipse.epf.uma:GuidanceDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-IfG3kKuJCWccQa0MByvCig" name="new_template,_MIBysDeoEdyFMtjeREc5MQ" guid="-IfG3kKuJCWccQa0MByvCig" changeDate="2011-07-14T13:26:38.750-0700" version=".1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>1.Executive Summary&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Provide a brief statement of the selected Reference Architecture and any major issues or risks.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>2. Introduction&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/strong>Provide introductory comments setting the context for the project etc.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>3. Key Drivers&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    Provide a brief statement of the business objectives or constraints.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>4. Architecture Requirements Checklist&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    Summarize the key architecture requirements using a standard checklist.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; bordercolor=&quot;#000000&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr bordercolor=&quot;#000000&quot; bgcolor=&quot;#CCCCCC&quot;>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;24%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    Requirement&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;24%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    Reference Architecture Characteristic&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;23%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    Required Value for Project&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;27%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    Risks/Issues/Comments/ Points to Investigate&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;tr bordercolor=&quot;#000000&quot; bgcolor=&quot;#ffffff&quot;>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;24%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    Requirement summary&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;24%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;br />&#xD;
                &lt;br />&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;23%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    Why important to the project.&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;27%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    Related issues, risks or notes.&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
&lt;/table>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;strong>5. Subject Area Checklist&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    This chapter compares the subject areas (domains) in the reference architecture with those required for the&#xD;
    engagement.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; bordercolor=&quot;#000000&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr bgcolor=&quot;#CCCCCC&quot;>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;159&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    Subject Area (Domain)&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;160&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    Present in Reference Architecture?&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;160&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    Required by New Architecture?&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;160&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    Issues/Risks/Notes&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;159&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    The subject area or domain.&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;160&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    Is the domain present in the reference Architecture (yes/no)?&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;160&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    Is the domain required in the new architecture (yes/no)?&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;160&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    Related issues, risks or notes.&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
&lt;/table>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>6. Statement of Fit&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Provide a summary of the extent of &quot;fit&quot; between the Reference Architecture and customer requirements. For each area&#xD;
    where the Reference Architecture does not meet requirements, describe briefly:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The unmet requirement.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The type and extent of delta that would be requisite for the Reference Architecture to meet the requirement. Should&#xD;
        it be extended, modified, or receive a new subject area?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        An estimate of the cost and risk of the delta.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
  <attachments>resources/umf_ref_arch_fit_gap_analysis.dot</attachments>
